  "texts": [
    "While the momentum and advocacy surrounding the fight against contract cheating is growing, the contract-cheating industry is experiencing stiff competition from GenAI (McColl, 2023), partly because the quality of GenAI-produced writing is decent enough to dupe the assessors and is done privately.",
    "The findings from this study support McColl's position.",
    "The AI-composed passages were sufficiently human-like, which is why humans' detection rate was so low (24%).",
    "Suppose the results from this study are corroborated in larger studies; in that case, human detective powers, professed by many, will need to be questioned.",
    "As the quality of GenAI improves, the automated detection will likely falter, as is evident in a recent investigation by Elkhatat et al. 2023. This conundrum squarely poses the problem of verifying whether a text is human-generated or AI-generated."
  ],
